news.title: Supertech twin towers demolition: Residents return to adjoining complexes
news.para: About 75 per cent of the ATS village and nearly half of the Emerald Court, the other residential complex just metres away from the demolished twin towers, are back.

news.title: Removal of Supertech twin towers debris to take 90 days: Edifice Engineering
news.para: A meeting with residents was held at the Emerald Court society in the afternoon by officials of Edifice Engineering, Jet Demolitions, Central Building Research Institute and the Noida Authority while Police Commissioner Alok Singh and Joint Commissioner Love Kumar were also present.

news.title: Punjab government to come out with real estate policy to check unplanned development
news.para: The cabinet minister assured the developers that all their legitimate demands will be considered sympathetically and he will discuss them with the chief minister.

news.title: Madras HC appoints mediator to solve conflict between builder & flat buyers
news.para: The petition sought to quash a case registered by the Central Crime Branch police for the offences including criminal conspiracy and cheating.

news.title: Gurugram civic body takes over Greenwood City
news.para: With the latest addition, MCG has taken charge of eight colonies, and the last pending — Mayfield Garden — will be done by September 7, officials said.

news.title: Macrotech Developers to raise up to Rs 250 crore through NCDs
news.para: The company did not disclose the utilisation of the proceeds of the proposed Non-Convertible Debentures (NCDs) issue.

news.title: Agricultural Bank of China's property bad loans jump 19% in H1 2022
news.para: AgBank's non-performing loan ratio for the sector hit 3.97% at the end of June, compared to the bank's overall NPL ratio of 1.41%, it said.

news.title: Why is AAI's decision relaxing building height restriction near Navi Mumbai airport illegal? HC asks petitioner
news.para: The court said while Shenoy has made oral arguments that the AAI's decision is not correct, it has failed to trace any pleading made on paper indicating the same was in violation of any statutory provisions.

news.title: Sebi overhauls preferential allotment rules for REITs, InvITs
news.para: ​Under the new framework, the pricing formula for allotment of units under preferential issue would be the Volume-Weighted Average Price (VWAP) of weekly highs and lows for 90 trading days or 10 trading days, whichever is higher.

news.title: Unauthorised colonies outside Panchkula will now get basic facilities
news.para: ​​A 6-month deadline has been given to legalise the illegal colonies. On the classification and criteria for application, the DTP said four categories have been formed.

news.title: Have completed 500 slabs for PMAY housing complex in 489 days: CIDCO
news.para: ​The residential complex for which these slabs have been cast is coming up in Taloja node of Navi Mumbai, an official said. We have been able to cast over one slab per day at this site using modern technology, he said.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC to take Rs 1,080 crore hit by not hiking property tax
news.para: The BMC is also forgoing Rs 462 crore due to the property tax waiver for those living in homes below 500 sq ft. This concession has been implemented from January 1 onwards. A total of 16.14 lakh residential flat owners have benefited from it.

news.title: Jaipur: Existing owners to get lease deeds at Nahargarh eco sensitive zone
news.para: After seeking directions from the forest department, the civic body is contemplating to issue lease deeds during the Prashasan Saharono Ke Sang camps to the houses situated 1-km beyond the sanctuary line.

news.title: Nagpur: Four months after revised layout plan submission, NIT orders verification
news.para: TOI on January 1, 2021, had reported that 317 plots owners are running pillar to post for constructing houses following construction of overhead water tank and road by the NIT on some part of many plots assuming them to be public utility (PU) land.

news.title: Centre's share for implementation of PMAY-G in Rajasthan falls to Rs 1,400 crore
news.para: In 2019-20, 3,76,446 houses were sanctioned under PMAY-G in Rajasthan, 2,72,186 houses in 2020-21 and 3,88,977 houses were sanctioned in 2021-22.
